data.name: checkBoxEncodingKeyFrameInterval.ToolTip
data.value: Gets or sets a time value between 0.5 to 20 seconds to specify the output fragment length for the video and audio tracks of an encoding live event. For the video track it also defines the key frame interval, or the length of a GoP (group of pictures). If this value is not set for an encoding live event, the fragment duration defaults to 2 seconds.

data.name: textBoxEncodingKeyFrameInterval.ToolTip
data.value: Gets or sets a time value between 0.5 to 20 seconds to specify the output fragment length for the video and audio tracks of an encoding live event. For the video track it also defines the key frame interval, or the length of a GoP (group of pictures). If this value is not set for an encoding live event, the fragment duration defaults to 2 seconds.
